<major-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/wms/2004-06-24a.65.0" nospeaker="true" colnum="65"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200304/ldhansrd/vo040624/text/40624-34.htm#40624-34_head2">
	Northern Ireland Strategic Investment Board: Report and Accounts 2003&ndash;04
</major-heading>

<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/wms/2004-06-24a.65.1" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100013" speakername="Baroness Amos" colon=":" colnum="65"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200304/ldhansrd/vo040624/text/40624-34.htm#40624-34_spmin0">
	<p pid="a.65.1/1">My honourable friend the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Northern Ireland has made the following Ministerial Statement:</p>
	<p pid="a.65.1/2">Today I have placed in the Libraries of the House copies of the report and accounts 2003&ndash;04 of the Strategic Investment Board for Northern Ireland.</p>
</speech>

<major-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/wms/2004-06-24a.65.2" nospeaker="true" colnum="65"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200304/ldhansrd/vo040624/text/40624-34.htm#40624-34_head3">
	Army Base Repair Organisation: Key Targets 2004&ndash;05
</major-heading>

<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/wms/2004-06-24a.65.3" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100030" speakername="Lord Bach" colon=":" colnum="65"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200304/ldhansrd/vo040624/text/40624-34.htm#40624-34_spmin1">
	<p pid="a.65.3/1">My right honourable friend the Minister of State for Defence (Mr Adam Ingram) has made the following Written Ministerial Statement.</p>
	<p pid="a.65.3/2">The following key targets have been set for the Army Base Repair Organisation for financial year 2004&ndash;05.</p>
	<table>
		<tbody>
			<tr pid="a.65.3/5"> <td>Key Target</td> <td>Details</td> <td>Target</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.65.3/6"> <td>KT 1&mdash;Financial Performance&mdash;Return on Capital Employed (ROCE).</td> <td>The measurement of ABRO's ROCE.</td> <td>To achieve a return, averaged over the period 1 April 2004 to 31 March 2005, of at least 3.5 per cent.</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.65.3/7"> <td>KT2&mdash;Delivery Performance.</td> <td>The measurement of revenue projection.</td> <td>To complete delivery of 100 per cent of the planned revenue projection (&pound;150 million) in FY 2004&ndash;05, and in each of the next three years.</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.65.3/8"> <td>KT3&mdash;Business Systems</td> <td>The measurement of the introduction and operation of TABS and the imperative to detach from the current supply system.</td> <td>To introduce and have operational the ABRO Business System (TABS) and to have detached from the ESPPA supply system by 31 March 2005.</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.65.3/9"> <td>KT4&mdash;Efficiency</td> <td>The measurement of the reduction in price of ABRO output.</td> <td>To reduce the average equipment repair price, across the whole programme, by 20 per cent against the 2002&ndash;03 baseline.</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.65.3/10"> <td>KT5&mdash;Winning Work</td> <td>The measurement of ABRO winning work.</td> <td>To maintain a closing order book of at least &pound;80   million for FY 2004&ndash;05, and to maintain this level for the next three years.</td> </tr>
		</tbody>
	</table>
</speech>

<major-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/wms/2004-06-24a.66.0" nospeaker="true" colnum="66"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200304/ldhansrd/vo040624/text/40624-34.htm#40624-34_head4">
	Elder Abuse
</major-heading>

<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/wms/2004-06-24a.66.1" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100670" speakername="Lord Warner" colon=":" colnum="66"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200304/ldhansrd/vo040624/text/40624-34.htm#40624-34_spmin2">
	<p pid="a.66.1/1">My honourable friend the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Community (Dr Stephen Ladyman) has made the following Written Ministerial Statement today.</p>
	<p pid="a.66.1/2">The Government's response to the Health Committee's Second Report of Session 2003&ndash;04 on elder abuse, Cm 6270, has been published today. Copies have been placed in the Library.</p>
</speech>

